Chemical-Specific Prevention Steps
The refinery has a number of safeguards that are used to protect personnel and property from the hazards of the covered processes. These safeguards were either originally constructed in the unit or implemented as a recommendation from a PHA, audit, or other avenue. These safeguards are examined during a PHA for their adequacy in detecting, preventing and/or mitigating any potential hazards of the process. If the PHA team determines that the safeguards do not adequately protect against a particular hazard, corrective actions are recommended.
As part of the PHA study, potential hazards and their safeguards are examined in a rigorous, methodical fashion for a variety of scenarios. The primary focus is on prevention of release. The following are examples of safeguards designed for prevention of a potential hazard:
